its been far too long..

 

this semester has really helped me put a lot of things into prospective...like, i dont want to major in business, im broke, i need a job, i need a new car, i need to get organized, and of course, i need to pass and keep my scholarships. boooo.v and lets see, ive probably royally fucked up many relationships and friendships ive had, because im broke and i cant afford to go places (like cornell and gt) im sorry i dont know what else to say. im a bad person, i know, i need to be like restrained from life.  :( 

 

ok well on a brighter note, juan and i went to the new amsterdams show at northstar last sunday.  i like that venue alot.  it feels like the troc to me, and i love LOVE LOVE the troc.  good times there.  anyway, im glad juan hasnt changed, i mean he has, but surprisingly for him, in a good way and i can stand to hang out him!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

 

im done, i miss everyone, but i love being away from home.  its amazing.  amazing. need i say more? although i have been craving a trip to the beach, i dont care how cold it is or will get, i need the smell of OCEAN CITYYYYYYYYYYYYY.

 

 

im going to art class now :-D

welllll, its been a good, oh say, 3 months i suppose since i thought twice about this thing? im watching futurama on tbs...its late, or is it early? either way, i cant sleep.  i can thank dan voss for reminding me i used to update this like it was my only job.  i feel like so much has changed in such a short amount of time.  i mean, courtneys gone, sullys gone, jackie and greg will be gone, then i will be gone, and brandon and jess...:(...didnt realize this would all happen so quickly.  but i mean, i guess its a good thing dan reminded me about this, now i can give him cool shout outs that no one else will understand.  like, "hey dan, im gunna come visit you at georgia tech and see one of your games, and where your sjp practice jersey and look like an ass".  see, no one else gets that!  anyway, i spent (and wasted) most of my summer in a cubical, in an office, not at the beach, making money...money that is long gone now, again, something wasted.  but thats besides the point. sean and i are still together.  has anyone ever seen that commercial for the FX show RESCUE ME with denis leary? the one thats the preview for season two, where hes just falling and thinking about everything thats going and has gone wrong? and everything that will go wrong? ahhh, thats how i feel right now.  i should be packing and gettin ready to move in next week, but ive taken numerous days to just drive to the shore for random reasons.  either way, what im trying to say is i am in no way ready to leave, or at least leave without going to the shore at least 2 more times.  im gettin real tired, me and j.d. had a nice evening, but i think i took advantage of him, but what else is new?? only gregs online, everyone else has lives! goodnight.

ahh the sweet smell of break....siiiigh....

if only i had somewhere to go haha...ive been busy, hence the lack of updating. not that i mind.  as much as i love bitching my life out on here, its much more fulfilling knowing im wasting my time pimping hoes and what not. (slight humor there). the past week has been awesome, im pretty sure ive seen people i love oh so much everyday, and people i care not to see have not been seen! this is a brand new accomplishment in my life.  patti and i are finally beginning to form stable grounds and the war flags are down for the moment.  i will actually have money tomorrow night, until then im living off of $4.87, plus i need gas :(.  bri's home from cornell, and i only got a chance to see him for a total of about 20 minutes after the friday night show of EVITA (ps....ITS FINALLY OVER) plus joeys down to visit him so a much needed visit is coming up in the next 18 hours (maybe breakfast??...i dunno) haha

 

yesterday katherine and i went out to a lovely lunch at tgi fridays.  appetizers are AMAZING, need i say more? asshole me left the window open while i was at school tho dropping off fashion show money, so my entire seat was soaked.  it was a lovely drive to pick up kate, to say the least.  i came home, cleaned my room after finding a gianormous spider in yesterday, then made dinner and kicked back watching M*A*S*H (haha i love this show, but it for me on dvd someone thaaaanks)ran to cvs, blockbuster, and picked up seean.  then i fell asleep on sully haha.  gotta love dinero tho in a bronx tale, oh and the italian accents, fuckin awesome haha.

 

so yeah, that leaves today...carless and no where to go anyway.  the best part about break is waking up and not knowing what day it is until i wake up and patti is not at work (signaling a weekend) i gotta go get easter shit tonight before church >:o its ok, pattis buyin so im happy.  i think thats it...i cant think im still sleeping. good mourning...

long, long, long, long, long, long, long, long, long, long, long, long day.  i really need to go to bed, but im feelin too sick and im making some ramen

so apparently i have anger issues.  i cant see why.  i mean, right now, yes im angry, but i have reason to be.  earlier today, i was grumpy, miserable and tired.  last night, same thing.  all im gunna say about right now is dan voss...i dont care how true any of it is, i just wanna know how it got started in the first place. 

other than the play, i swung by katies for chirs' party (happy 18th big boy hahah) then went to see sean (no gay babies were made though, sorry guys) haha....

 

 

ps...in response to brian "yes, i can truffle shuffle and im damn good at it" pleis' post, i have decided on a prom date mwahaha...so SUCK IT :P

beoynd bored and sick.  i think its just this time of year that makes me feel like total shit (by this time of year i mean the play/pre-spring break) tiger face grrrr....so yeah night 2 of evita..better than night 1...2 shows down and only 6 more to go. thats all im saying about it :X

 

i feel like absolute shit.  ill have a sinus infection by monday i promise you. i think im gunna get sick.  i really need sleep, and to not wake up at 5am for once.  and i need to find a prom date more than anything else.  and i think i know who im gunna ask...actually at this point i KNOW who im gunna ask, but not quite yet haha.  dont ask...

 

nothing else to say...

i got  my license...need i say more?...

 

...goodday for the most part, i dunno why, im still feeling overly tired and down, but im living on caffeine rushes still from the play, so hopefully that will die down.  i dont really know what else to say, this things been down the past week or so, or i would have had many angry entries in here.  im calming myself down, slowly and surely. very slowly, not so surely. ive got a lot goin thru my head, but honestly, what else is new? i know i say the same things over and over.  the truth is i dont remember what i was supposed to bring jimmy into work tomorrow to show him, and i was with him only 2 hours ago?? goddamn, i suck, haha, does this mean im dying, since i cant remember things?   we dont have school tomrrow, but im bored and i cant sleep.  i have no book to read, i have no food to eat, im slowly dying. heres a good question though...if i bought a car stereo could someone install it for me?????? come on guys i know at least 2 people who know how to do this i think...

 

as i sit here updating this thing, completely freezing, i now wish i had gotten out of the car and bought a cappacino (excuse the spelling) from WAWA.  damn the fucking cold.

HOME ON A SATURDAY NIGHT!!! grrrrrr

ok well to simple recap the past 36 hours, in one word that is, SHITTY, to say the least.  and the only reason i am updating is because i really dont feel like IMing this whole thing to bri (because hes ALWAYS away! GOD!) haha ok soooooo....recalling sundays nights head injury, apparently it can take days for the symptoms to have an effect.  hence in my case. wednesday. so terrible.  first of all, groundhogs day, ive hated it for exactly ten years now, and now, NOW i hate it with even more fire and vengence.  so i go to school, find out i failed readers class for the 2nd quarter (no comment on that now) and i go to the nurse, thinknig ill just go home sick bc i felt like shit anyway.  well, my mom gets there and announces that i will not be going home, but rather to the ER.  GOODY! well, 3 hours later, after sitting in the MOST uncomfortable chair ive ever sat in, and getting sick in the waiting room while watching ER on tv, with a little baby crying in my ear, i am taken to a room to sleep on a very uncomfrtable bed.  i have to pee in a cup, put a freakin gown on, and eat terrible hospital food.  this ordeal began at 11am, by this point, its 530. i get a CT and a lovely IV in my left hand, to go with the scrapped up wirst.  by 830, im discharged with a nice load of sedatives to keep me happy for hours on end (no refill unfortuantely), anyway, i sleep for exactly 12 hours because ray calls me at 930 this morning (???? i dont even know) to wake me up haha...but now im home, for at least another 24 hours to my dismay, meaning i cannot do anything tomorrow night and for the most part all weekend :( talk about a total buzz kill. geez.  buuut if anyone wants to give up their friday night plans to come over, i would owe you my first born child :)

 

other than that, nothing is really up. i mean, im just rethinknig a lotta things at this point (ahem boys). i dont know, maybe its me, maybe its the thought of starting something and either not wanting it to end or just not being ready. yeah i said it.  i nkow someone understands me here.  i try, i get busy, and i NEED to do this other stuff.  im sorry. everyone can just hate me.  i know, and now i have a headache because everythings my fault again, and now the vein in my left hand is swelling >:o

HATE ME I DARE YOU!!!!!!

 

so, bri, in case you were wondering, THAT is why i never called you back, im sorry babe, ill ttyl tho because now im going to beeeed again

 

on that note hahahahahahahaha...ray you owe me and evy BIG TIME

ok im not one to post daily, but this..this NEEDED to be posted...

WARNING!: the following story may offend certain people, especially those who fight for the rights of senior citizens

so today at work (meadowbrook), jen and i are putting the nuts in containers (literally), and this old man walks in, holding his ass.  he asks jen and i if we have a bathroom because its "an emergency".  jen and i answer politely "yeah but its only for employees". well, this guy, doesnt take no for an answer, walks back and starts asking steve, the owner, where the bathroom is, still holding his ass mind you.  steve, after much hesitation, lets the man use the bathroom.  15-20 minutes later, the man emerges from the room, and just walks out. no goodbye, no cya later, no notthing.  later on, steve goes into the bathroom to empty the trash and finds a wonderful present left for him.  dare i tell??? well, in the words of the great TOM DELONGE, soiled undergarments.  yes.  steve, being completely italian, completely loses it, and i must say, mike dunican, you picked an awful day to take off. hahaha. 

i would now like to aplogize to everyone that offended, but im sorry, it had to be told.  and many of you are probably wondering why, but its kinda like a had-to-be-there-thing, but the fact that the old man was tear-ing and steve was still hesistant just made work at meadwobrook all the more meaningful for me.  can you tell ive become a very angry person??

anyway, theres my bitter angst story gone hilariously amusing with the help of steve and old man, and jens obnoxious laugh (which i love..)

so, ive been thinking, ALOT. and, as much as i dont like to admit it, at this point, i hate life.  no lie.  this is me being optimistic.______________________see...its not working well. for starters, i suck, i know, im sorry i left deannas party, imsorry i tried to do something good, but i cant put on this face anymore. yeah i walked out and completely lied and said i was coming back...i had no intention of returning, im sorry. i know i cant apoligize enough and i am sorry for not coming back, but i couldnt stay there, plus, i have been so detached from that group of friends its not even funny, and i needed to clear my head.   i needed to get out desperately.  wayne, PA did wonders for me tonight, it was so far from jersey and from everyone.  and now i have a headache.  i was praying for a car crash on the way home (sorry jackie)  but now, im thinking, and death probably would have solved so many of lifes problems.  i know, its the easy way out according to rusty, and yeah, it is, but is it a bad thing to think thats the only way to solve problems? obviously it is..  ok, theres no one i can talk to because no one knows the everything.  i know i need to talk to some people, and by some people i mean about 10 people, because i have completely and utterly blown them off, and for the record i do not check my voicemails more than once every two weeks.  and you know, heres the worst thing...ive tried so hard to get over certain people and act like they mean nothing to me, or at least i tell myself that numerously times at one shot, but, in all honestly, im pretty sure that if you were take out a whole big part of my life, i would be alot happeir right now.  i know things arent any better for anyone else, and that no one cares to hear me bitch, but i really dont give a shit.  im too lazy to write anything down on paper for only myself to see and read back so i know whats going thru my head at certain times, so this is just a time and tree saver. and if i dont write things out, i cant solve anything.  im useless like that.  wow, none of this will make sense to anyone, but it means the world to me.  so yeah.
